comments.body:
When I tried creating security group with description 
{code}
asdgasgag!@@#$@#%$#^%$#^%$&^%&^%**&^(*&^)*&(_(*)+()+)~`,/<>?<>?<{}[][][\|}{
{code}

I got the followingmessage: 

"Description is required, must be between 1 and 255 characters, and may only contain letters, numbers, spaces, and select special characters"

[~jloza] Please specify what special characters must be excluded.

[~alice], [~jloza]: According to http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/ec2/create-security-group.html, the special characters allowed in a VPC security group are...

{code}
a-z, A-Z, 0-9, spaces, and ._-:/()#,@[]+=;{}!$*
{code}

I'm open to ideas on how to communicate that in a non-ugly way.

[~jloza]: We have a validation notice for roles...

{code}
Role names must be between 1 and 64 characters long, and may contain letters, numbers, '+', '=', ',', '.'. '@' and '-', and cannot contain spaces.
{code}

But that message is fugly and is potentially problematic for translators, which is why I suggested we not specify all the allowed special chars for VPC security groups.  The validation feedback kicks in when a non-valid character is typed, and since a user is unlikely to enter more than one invalid character before validation kicks in, I suggest we leave the wording as is.

[~jloza]: I had assumed you were fine with the existing validation message for security groups...

{code}
Description is required, must be between 1 and 255 characters, and may only contain letters, numbers, spaces, and select special characters
{code}

However, your last comment to Alice indicates you want the message to be similar to the following...

{code}
Description is required, must be between 1 and 255 characters, and may only contain letters, numbers, spaces, and the following characters: ._-:/()#,@[]+=;{}!$*
{code}

Could you clarify if that's the case?
